text.text:
The food was absolutely amazing—each dish was thoughtfully prepared with clear attention to the quality and detail of the ingredients. The flavors were well-balanced, making for a truly memorable dining experience.

However, the service could be improved. While the staff were efficient, they seemed to lack warmth and smiles, which impacted the overall atmosphere. A more welcoming and friendly attitude from the service team would enhance the dining experience significantly.

text.text: No reservation, but Bernadnette, the operations manager, kindly helped us find an indoor table. The food was amazing - veggie brekkie was delicious, especially the baked tomatoes, and the melon mangosteen cake and lemon loaf cake were fragrant and yummy without being too sweet. Our waiter was attentive and kept our water glasses full. We loved that we could linger for almost 5 hours without being rushed. Highly recommend!

text.text:
Managed to walk in on Sun morning without any reservation. For the portobello toast, not quite used to having French toast with savoury notes, but the avocado toast was nice. Scrambled eggs retained a creamy texture, yum. Portions were huge.

Loved visiting in the day with the daylight coming through.

text.text:
It was my first time dining at this café after discovering it on TikTok. I ordered the crispy Brussels sprouts and the wood-roasted pork chop, which were recommended by the staff. The Brussels sprouts were quite good at first, though they turned out to be a bit too spicy for my taste and started to feel a little salty after a while.

I was a bit disappointed with the wood-roasted pork chop—it didn’t quite live up to the recommendation. That might just be a matter of personal taste between me and my friend, but it lacked that “wow” factor and didn’t really have a strong meaty flavor.

On a brighter note, the ambience was really nice, which made the overall dining experience more pleasant. Maybe I’ll give some of the other dishes a try next time.

text.text: I came with my boyfriend for dinner, and the experience was amazing. The octopus was super tender, the chicken was delicious, and the sauce was incredible! What really surprised me was the rice pudding dessert—the texture of the puffed rice gave it a unique touch, and the balance of salty and sweet flavors was just perfect. We’ll definitely be back. Everything was absolutely delicious!
